3. Sempronio Blceso. The name of Blaesus was one of ill omen to the Romans in these parts. In the first Punic war (B.C. 253), C. Sempronius Blaesus the consul, being in command of 260 ships, his fleet ran aground on the Syrtis, and was only got off by throwiug everything overboard. 150 ships of the same fleet were afterwards lost on their way home, in a storm offCape Palinurus.
